Standar error for proportion of selection by bootstraping subjects

## mean + se
data.sem.e2 <- 
    data.ch.e2 |>
  count(subjid, phase, speaker, choice, name = "N") |>
  tidyr::complete(
    nesting(subjid, phase, speaker),
    choice,
    fill = list(N = 0)
  ) |>
  mutate(prop = N / 6) |>
  nest(data = -c(subjid))

# run resampling
set.seed(74)
coef.sem.e2 <- replicate(1000, {
  slice_sample(data.sem.e2, n = 44, replace = TRUE) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    group_by(speaker, phase, choice) |>    
    summarize(mprop = mean(prop), .groups = "drop")        
}, simplify = FALSE)  

# data frame with sem
bound.sem.e2<- coef.sem.e2 |>
  bind_rows(.id = "iteration") |> 
  select(speaker, phase, choice, mprop) |>
  group_by(speaker, phase, choice) |>
  summarize(
    sem_low = mean(mprop) + sd(mprop),
    sem_upp = mean(mprop) - sd(mprop),
    .groups = "drop"
  )

# data frame
df.choice.e2 <-
  data.ch.e2 |>
  filter(choice %in% c("named", "unnamed")) |>
  mutate(
    c.speaker = as.numeric(ifelse(speaker == "SpeakerA", -.5, .5)),
    c.phase = as.numeric(ifelse(phase == "Control", -.5, .5)),
    unnasel = as.numeric(ifelse(choice == "unnamed", 1,0))) |>
  select(respid, subjid, itemid, c.speaker, c.phase, unnasel) |>
  arrange(subjid, c.speaker, c.phase)


# model
model <- glmer(unnasel ~ c.speaker*c.phase +  
                 (1|subjid) + (1|itemid), df.choice.e2, na.action=na.omit,
               family=binomial, control=glmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa"))

# data frame

data1.eye.e2 <-
    data0.eye.e2 |> 
    mutate(
    speaker = case_when(
      condname %in% c("SpeakerA-Control", "SpeakerA-Experimental") ~ "SpeakerA",
      condname %in% c("SpeakerB-Control", "SpeakerB-Experimental") ~ "SpeakerB"),    
  phase = case_when(
      condname %in% c("SpeakerA-Control", "SpeakerB-Control" ) ~ "Control",
      condname %in% c("SpeakerA-Experimental", "SpeakerB-Experimental") ~ "Experimental")) |>
  group_by(subjid, phase, speaker, aoi, bin) |>
  summarize(meanp = mean(p), .groups = "drop") |>
  select(everything(), ms = bin) |>
  ungroup()
  
  

# smooth data by subjects ## 
data2.eye.e2 <- 
  data1.eye.e2 |>
  filter(ms >= 0, ms <= 3000) |>
  pivot_wider(names_from = aoi, values_from = meanp) |>
    group_by(subjid, phase, speaker) |>
    arrange(subjid, phase, speaker, ms) |> 
      mutate(
      nameds = {
        fit <- loess(named ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 0.6)
        predict(fit, ms)},
      unnameds = {
        fit <- loess(unnamed ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 0.6)
        predict(fit, ms)},
      unseens = {
        fit <- loess(unseen ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 0.6)
        predict(fit, ms)},
      seens = {
        fit <- loess(seen ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 0.6)
        predict(fit, ms)},
      blanks = {
        fit <- loess(blank ~ ms, data = cur_data(), span = 0.6)
        predict(fit, ms)},
    diff = unnamed - named,
    diffis = unnameds - nameds,
  ) |>
  ungroup()

Find clusters

# find cluster in real data
data.real <- 
  data.to0 |>
  unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    ungroup()

#clust.real.pval <-
cluster.real0 <-
  data.real |> 
  group_by(ms) |>  # Fit one model per `ms` group
  summarise(
    model = list(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.phase, data = cur_data())),  # One model per `ms`
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    model_summary = map(model, tidy)  # Extract coefficient details for each term
  ) |> 
  unnest(model_summary) |>  # Expand model coefficients
  select(ms, term, estimate, statistic, p.value) |>  # Keep relevant statistics
  mutate(
    sig = ifelse(p.value >= 0.05, 0, 1)
  ) |> 
  group_by(term) |>  # Group by model terms (Intercept, speaker, etc.)
  mutate(
    cluster = cumsum(
      sig != lag(sig, default = first(sig)) | 
      sign(statistic) != lag(sign(statistic), default = sign(first(statistic)))
    )
  ) |>
  group_by(cluster, sig, term) |> 
  summarise(
    start_ms = min(ms),
    end_ms = max(ms),
    n_ms = n(),
    mean_value = mean(statistic),
    sum_value = sum(statistic),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |>
  arrange(term) |>
  filter(sig==1)


saveRDS(cluster.real0, "../data/cluster.real0.e2.rds")

Cluster permutation (only for the intercept)

# data frame and variables for resampling
nsubj <- data.to0 |> distinct(subjid) |> count() |> pull()
counter <- 0
set.seed(74)

# resampling
coef.reg <- replicate(10000, {

  data.to <- data.to0 |>
    shuffle_each(c.phase, subjid) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |> ungroup()
  
data.to |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarize(
    t_value_intercept = map_dbl(
      .x = list(cur_data()), 
      ~ summary(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.phase, data = .x))$coefficients["(Intercept)", "t value"]
    )
  )  

}, simplify = FALSE)


# get data for each iteration
dist1 <- coef.reg |> bind_rows(.id = "iteration")

# pivot wide
dist2 <-
  dist1 |> 
   select(iteration, ms, t_value_intercept) |>
    pivot_wider(names_from = iteration, values_from = t_value_intercept)


## recode based on quantile
# extract ms column separately
ms_col <- dist2$ms

# convert to matrix for efficiency (excluding ms column)
dist_matrix <- as.matrix(dist2[ , !names(dist2) %in% "ms"])

# compute row-wise quantiles 
q95 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.95)
q05 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.05)

# apply conditions using matrix operations
flags_matrix <- (dist_matrix > q95) - (dist_matrix < q05)

# convert back to data frame
flags <- as.data.frame(flags_matrix)

# insert ms as the first column
flags <- cbind(ms = ms_col, flags)


# convert to data.table
flags_dt <- as.data.table(flags)


## find clusters in permuted dataset 
# reshape to long format (process in chunks if necessary)
clusters_dt <- melt(flags_dt, id.vars = "ms", variable.name = "column", value.name = "value", verbose = FALSE)

# convert column names to character for consistency
clusters_dt[, column := as.character(column)]

# compute cluster IDs using efficient vectorized operations
clusters_dt[, cluster := cumsum(value != shift(value, type = "lag", fill = first(value))), by = column]

# summarize clusters efficiently
clusters <- clusters_dt[, .(
  start_ms = first(ms),
  end_ms = last(ms),
  n_points = .N
), by = .(column, cluster, value)]

# convert `dist2` to `data.table` for fast filtering
dist2_dt <- as.data.table(dist2)

# reduce memory by selecting only relevant columns
dist2_dt <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", unique(clusters$column)), with = FALSE]

# process sum_abs_values in **chunks** to avoid memory overload
batch_size <- 500  # Adjust this based on available RAM
unique_columns <- unique(clusters$column)
sum_abs_values_list <- list()

for (i in seq(1, length(unique_columns), by = batch_size)) {
  batch_cols <- unique_columns[i:min(i + batch_size - 1, length(unique_columns))]
  
  # filter relevant data for the batch
  batch_dist2 <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", batch_cols), with = FALSE]

  # compute sum of absolute values efficiently in batches
  batch_sums <- clusters[column %in% batch_cols, .(
    sum_abs_values = sum(abs(batch_dist2[ms %between% c(start_ms, end_ms), get(column)]), na.rm = TRUE)
  ), by = .(column, cluster)]
  
  sum_abs_values_list[[length(sum_abs_values_list) + 1]] <- batch_sums
}

# combine batch results
sum_abs_values <- rbindlist(sum_abs_values_list)

# merge results back into `clusters`
clusters <- merge(clusters, sum_abs_values, by = c("column", "cluster"), all.x = TRUE)


# get distribution
mass.st0 <- 
  clusters |>
    ungroup() |>
    filter(value != 0) |>
    group_by(column) |>
    arrange(column, desc(sum_abs_values)) |>
    slice(1) |>
    pull(sum_abs_values)

  arrange(itemid, c.phase, c.speaker, ms) |>
  nest(data = -c("itemid", "c.phase")) |>
  arrange(itemid)

Find clusters by item

# find cluster in real data
data.reali <- 
  data.to0i |>
  unnest(cols = c(data)) |>
    ungroup()

#clust.real.pval <-
cluster.real0i <-
  data.reali |> 
  group_by(ms) |>  # Fit one model per `ms` group
  summarise(
    model = list(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.phase, data = cur_data())),  # One model per `ms`
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |> 
  mutate(
    model_summary = map(model, tidy)  # Extract coefficient details for each term
  ) |> 
  unnest(model_summary) |>  # Expand model coefficients
  select(ms, term, estimate, statistic, p.value) |>  # Keep relevant statistics
  mutate(
    sig = ifelse(p.value >= 0.05, 0, 1)
  ) |> 
  group_by(term) |>  # Group by model terms (Intercept, speaker, etc.)
  mutate(
    cluster = cumsum(
      sig != lag(sig, default = first(sig)) | 
      sign(statistic) != lag(sign(statistic), default = sign(first(statistic)))
    )
  ) |>
  group_by(cluster, sig, term) |> 
  summarise(
    start_ms = min(ms),
    end_ms = max(ms),
    n_ms = n(),
    mean_value = mean(statistic),
    sum_value = sum(statistic),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |>
  arrange(term) |>
  filter(sig==1)


saveRDS(cluster.real0i, "../data/cluster.real0i.e2.rds")

Cluster permutation by item (only for the intercept)

# data frame and variables for resampling
nitem <- data.to0i |> distinct(itemid) |> count() |> pull()
counter <- 0
set.seed(74)

# resampling
coef.regi <- replicate(10000, {

  data.to <- data.to0i |>
    shuffle_each(c.phase, itemid) |>
    unnest(cols = c(data)) |> ungroup()
  
data.to |> 
  group_by(ms) |> 
  summarize(
    t_value_intercept = map_dbl(
      .x = list(cur_data()), 
      ~ summary(lm(diffis ~ c.speaker * c.phase, data = .x))$coefficients["(Intercept)", "t value"]
    )
  )  

}, simplify = FALSE)


# get data for each iteration
dist1i <- coef.regi |> bind_rows(.id = "iteration")

# pivot wide
dist2 <-
  dist1i |> 
   select(iteration, ms, t_value_intercept) |>
    pivot_wider(names_from = iteration, values_from = t_value_intercept)


## recode based on quantile
# extract ms column separately
ms_col <- dist2$ms

# convert to matrix for efficiency (excluding ms column)
dist_matrix <- as.matrix(dist2[ , !names(dist2) %in% "ms"])

# compute row-wise quantiles 
q95 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.95)
q05 <- apply(dist_matrix, 1, quantile, probs = 0.05)

# apply conditions using matrix operations
flags_matrix <- (dist_matrix > q95) - (dist_matrix < q05)

# convert back to data frame
flags <- as.data.frame(flags_matrix)

# insert ms as the first column
flags <- cbind(ms = ms_col, flags)


# convert to data.table
flags_dt <- as.data.table(flags)


## find clusters in permuted dataset 
# reshape to long format (process in chunks if necessary)
clusters_dt <- melt(flags_dt, id.vars = "ms", variable.name = "column", value.name = "value", verbose = FALSE)

# convert column names to character for consistency
clusters_dt[, column := as.character(column)]

# compute cluster IDs using efficient vectorized operations
clusters_dt[, cluster := cumsum(value != shift(value, type = "lag", fill = first(value))), by = column]

# summarize clusters efficiently
clusters <- clusters_dt[, .(
  start_ms = first(ms),
  end_ms = last(ms),
  n_points = .N
), by = .(column, cluster, value)]

# convert `dist2` to `data.table` for fast filtering
dist2_dt <- as.data.table(dist2)

# reduce memory by selecting only relevant columns
dist2_dt <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", unique(clusters$column)), with = FALSE]

# process sum_abs_values in **chunks** to avoid memory overload
batch_size <- 500  # Adjust this based on available RAM
unique_columns <- unique(clusters$column)
sum_abs_values_list <- list()

for (i in seq(1, length(unique_columns), by = batch_size)) {
  batch_cols <- unique_columns[i:min(i + batch_size - 1, length(unique_columns))]
  
  # filter relevant data for the batch
  batch_dist2 <- dist2_dt[, c("ms", batch_cols), with = FALSE]

  # compute sum of absolute values efficiently in batches
  batch_sums <- clusters[column %in% batch_cols, .(
    sum_abs_values = sum(abs(batch_dist2[ms %between% c(start_ms, end_ms), get(column)]), na.rm = TRUE)
  ), by = .(column, cluster)]
  
  sum_abs_values_list[[length(sum_abs_values_list) + 1]] <- batch_sums
}

# combine batch results
sum_abs_values <- rbindlist(sum_abs_values_list)

# merge results back into `clusters`
clustersi <- merge(clusters, sum_abs_values, by = c("column", "cluster"), all.x = TRUE)


# get distribution
mass.st0i <- 
  clustersi |>
    ungroup() |>
    filter(value != 0) |>
    group_by(column) |>
    arrange(column, desc(sum_abs_values)) |>
    slice(1) |>
    pull(sum_abs_values)
